---
import CaseStudyMedia from './CaseStudyMedia.astro';
import { uroborosCaseStudyImages } from '../../data/uroborosCaseStudy';
import { aboutContactIcons } from '../../data/aboutAssets';
import { contactEmail, socialLinks } from '../../data/aboutContent';

const images = uroborosCaseStudyImages;

const backToChapterHref = '/?highlight=uroboros#chapter-1';
---

<article class="scarlett-case-study uroboros-case-study">
  <header class="scarlett-case-study__hero">
    <p class="scarlett-case-study__project-name">Uroboros</p>
    <h1 class="scarlett-case-study__hero-title">
      A puzzle-platformer about turning a finite set of instructions into <strong>recursive chains</strong> of movement, combat, and choice.
    </h1>
    <div class="scarlett-case-study__hero-split" data-uroboros-hero-split>
      <div class="scarlett-case-study__hero-copy" data-uroboros-hero-copy>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          Players assemble commands to guide an explorer through compact cosmic levels. By combining basic actions, directional modifiers, loops, and grouped execution, a small instruction set produces increasingly complex outcomes.
        </p>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          Uroboros was created by a seven-person team in 48 hours for CiGA Game Jam 2024 under the theme Limited and Limitless. I was responsible for game design and level design.
        </p>
      </div>
      <figure class="scarlett-case-study__hero-media" data-uroboros-hero-media>
        <img
          class="scarlett-case-study__hero-img"
          src={images.hero}
          alt=""
          loading="eager"
          decoding="async"
          data-uroboros-hero-img
        />
      </figure>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="scarlett-case-study__section" aria-labelledby="uroboros-inspiration">
    <p id="uroboros-inspiration" class="scarlett-case-study__section-label">INSPIRATION</p>

    <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">
      Finite Rules, Expanding Possibilities
    </h2>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__uroboros-inspiration-split">
      <CaseStudyMedia
        class="scarlett-case-study__uroboros-inspiration-media scarlett-case-study__transparent-media"
        src={images.inspirationShapedPrimary}
        alt=""
        placeholder="Inspiration image"
      />
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__body scarlett-case-study__uroboros-inspiration-copy">
        The theme <em>Limited and Limitless</em> led us to explore how a small set of rules could generate a wide range of outcomes. Inspired by neural signalling, we designed simple commands that could be connected, modified, and repeated to produce complex behaviour.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scarlett-case-study__section" aria-labelledby="uroboros-game-design">
    <p id="uroboros-game-design" class="scarlett-case-study__section-label">GAME DESIGN</p>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__stack">
      <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
        <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">
          Programming Movement
        </h2>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          Players construct an instruction sequence before putting it into action. Basic commands control movement and attacks, while modifiers, loops, and grouped execution transform short sequences into more complex behaviours.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ul class="scarlett-case-study__rule-list">
        <li class="scarlett-case-study__rule-item">
          <span class="scarlett-case-study__rule-number">01</span>
          <div class="scarlett-case-study__rule-copy">
            <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-body"><strong>Basic Actions</strong>Independent commands control movement, jumping, and attacks, with each action applying a fixed force in a defined direction.</p>
            <CaseStudyMedia
              class="scarlett-case-study__uroboros-rule-media scarlett-case-study__transparent-media"
              src={images.gameDesignImage1}
              alt=""
              placeholder="Basic Actions"
              fit="contain"
            />
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="scarlett-case-study__rule-item">
          <span class="scarlett-case-study__rule-number">02</span>
          <div class="scarlett-case-study__rule-copy">
            <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-body"><strong>Directional Modifiers</strong>Modifiers redirect a movement or attack command, but cannot be executed independently.</p>
            <CaseStudyMedia
              class="scarlett-case-study__uroboros-rule-media scarlett-case-study__transparent-media"
              src={images.gameDesignImage2}
              alt=""
              placeholder="Directional Modifiers"
              fit="contain"
            />
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="scarlett-case-study__rule-item">
          <span class="scarlett-case-study__rule-number">03</span>
          <div class="scarlett-case-study__rule-copy">
            <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-body"><strong>Loop</strong>The Loop repeats every instruction to its left, including itself, allowing short sequences to expand recursively.</p>
            <CaseStudyMedia
              class="scarlett-case-study__uroboros-rule-media scarlett-case-study__transparent-media"
              src={images.gameDesignImage3}
              alt=""
              placeholder="Loop"
              fit="contain"
            />
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="scarlett-case-study__rule-item">
          <span class="scarlett-case-study__rule-number">04</span>
          <div class="scarlett-case-study__rule-copy">
            <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-body"><strong>Combine</strong>The Combine command groups a set number of following instructions and executes them as a stronger combined action.</p>
            <CaseStudyMedia
              class="scarlett-case-study__uroboros-rule-media scarlett-case-study__transparent-media"
              src={images.gameDesignImage4}
              alt=""
              placeholder="Combine"
              fit="contain"
            />
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scarlett-case-study__section" aria-labelledby="uroboros-game-development">
    <p id="uroboros-game-development" class="scarlett-case-study__section-label">
      LEVEL DESIGN
    </p>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
      <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">
        Multiple Routes, Different Risks
      </h2>
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
        Deceleration zones, vertical jumps, enemies, and alternate routes require players to balance speed against precision. A faster path may demand tighter timing, while a safer route may require a longer and more carefully constructed sequence.
      </p>
      <CaseStudyMedia
        class="scarlett-case-study__uroboros-level-media scarlett-case-study__uroboros-level-media--full scarlett-case-study__transparent-media"
        src={images.levelDesignImage1}
        alt=""
        placeholder="Level design overview"
        aspectRatio="858 / 224"
        fit="contain"
      />
    </div>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
      <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">
        Finite Spaces, Expanding Solutions
      </h2>
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
        Each level is compact, but the instruction system creates multiple ways through it. By combining actions, modifiers, and loops, players transform a fixed layout into a space of branching solutions.
      </p>
      <CaseStudyMedia
        class="scarlett-case-study__uroboros-level-media scarlett-case-study__uroboros-level-media--feature scarlett-case-study__transparent-media"
        src={images.levelDesignImage2}
        alt=""
        placeholder="Level design scene"
        aspectRatio="467 / 259"
        fit="contain"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="scarlett-case-study__footer">
    <a class="scarlett-case-study__back" href={backToChapterHref}>← Back to Chapter</a>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__closing">
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__thanks">
        Thank you for exploring my world! If it resonates, I'd love to hear from you.
      </p>
      <div class="scarlett-case-study__credit">
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__name">Hang Wan</span>
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__credit-dot" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__role">Design Playful Experience</span>
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__credit-divider" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <div class="scarlett-case-study__credit-links">
          <a
            class="scarlett-case-study__credit-link"
            href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}
            aria-label="Email Hang Wan"
          >
            <img
              class="scarlett-case-study__credit-icon"
              src={aboutContactIcons.gmail}
              alt=""
              width="44"
              height="44"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </a>
          <a
            class="scarlett-case-study__credit-link"
            href={socialLinks.linkedin}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            aria-label="LinkedIn"
          >
            <img
              class="scarlett-case-study__credit-icon"
              src={aboutContactIcons.linkedin}
              alt=""
              width="44"
              height="44"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</article>

<script>
  function initCaseStudyMedia() {
    document.querySelectorAll('[data-case-study-img]').forEach((img) => {
      if (!(img instanceof HTMLImageElement) || img.dataset.mediaBound === 'true') return;
      img.dataset.mediaBound = 'true';

      const markMissing = () => {
        const figure = img.closest('[data-case-study-media]');
        figure?.classList.add('is-missing');
      };

      img.addEventListener('error', markMissing);
      if (img.complete && img.naturalWidth === 0) markMissing();
    });
  }

  initCaseStudyMedia();
  document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', initCaseStudyMedia);
</script>
